ctions, a series of analyses both criticizing and defending the decisions in Bush v. Gore, American perspectives on the Florida struggle and America's electoral system, and a debate on maintaining or reforming the electoral college. The authors include participants in the legal and political battles surrounding the Florida election, foreigners charged with monitoring and supervising elections, and scholars from many disciplines specializing in constitutionalism, democracy, and American election law.Contributors  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aElection lawxUnited States. 0aElection lawzUnited States. 0aPresidentsxElectionx2000xUnited States. 0aPresidentszUnited StatesxElectiony2000. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  a2000.  aal gore.  aamerican history.  aballots.  aconstitution.  aconstitutional.  ademocracy.  aelection year.  aelections.  aelectoral college.  aequal protection.  aessay collection.  ageorge bush.  ahistorical.  alaw.  alegal issues.  apolemics.  apolitics.  apresidential candidates.  apresidential elections.  aunited states history.  aus history.  avoter suppression.  avoters.  avoting.1 aAckerman, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvineri, Shlomo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBennett, Robert W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBest, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrady, Henry E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrookhiser, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDworkin, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFletcher, George P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l